description:
&lt;p&gt;CARDIAC INVESTIGATIONS DEPT&lt;br /&gt;SENIOR INTERVENTIONAL CARDIAC PHYSIOLOGIST– A4C BAND 6-7&lt;br /&gt;17.5% RECRUITMENT AND RETENTION BONUS&lt;br /&gt;37.5 HOURS PER WEEK&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for an additional Band 6 or 7 Interventional Physiologist to join our dynamic interventional team. We have developed our services to include:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• A Physiologist-led Pacing and High Voltage service with extensive home monitoring and large numbers of new implants of brady, tachy and CRT devices including SICD.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Community hospital clinics and home visits for many of our pacemaker patients.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• A comprehensive Heart Failure service as part of a truly multi-disciplinary team, including Physiologist-led CRT optimisation and follow up.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Provision of a 24/7 Primary PCI service to the South East Midlands area.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• High volume complex PCI with routine use of laser, rotablation IVUS and OCT delivered through 3 cath labs.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Physiologists implanting Reveals.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have a modern digital echo lab performing the full range of complex scans, satellite pacing and echo clinics, and the support of 9 proactive Cardiologists.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The right candidate will have BSc in Clinical Physiology and the ability to work unsupervised in the Catheter Laboratory, providing technical support for the full range of procedures. In return, we will pay a permanent 17.5% Recruitment and Retention bonus and will offer you significant exposure to highly specialised and complex procedures to develop your skills and qualifications. CPD is actively encouraged and funded. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Our PPCI on call commitment is approximately 1 in 7 and we actively encourage flexible hours with most of our interventional staff choosing to work 8-6 for 4 days a week.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There is easy road access to much of the country with London 50mins away by rail. The beautiful residential towns of Stamford, Market Harborough and Uppingham are all within easy reach of the hospital, as is the City of Leicester which is known for its shopping, culture and leisure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leanne Kelly, Senior Chief Cardiac Physiologist for the Interventional position (01536 492542 leanne.kelly1@nhs.net)&lt;/p&gt;
